sooo i havent posted in like forever... so i thought what better way to start again, than posting with a ridiculous survey about last year.

1.) Where did you ring in 2007? well i was at amy and james for a bit and then i went over to anne and davids.

2.) What was your status by Valentine's Day? alone.

3.) Were you in school (anytime this year)? yes... like the entire time... boo

4.) How did you earn your keep? i dont. except when i work at camp in the summer.. but it doesnt do much.

5.) Did you have to go to the hospital? Nope

6.) Did you encounter the police? No.

7.) Where did you go on vacation? camp.. not much of a vacation.

8.) What did you purchase that was over $500? nothing 

9.) Did you know anybody who got married? no

10.) Do you know anybody who passed away? no

11.) Have you run into anybody you graduated high school with? haha YES. just last week i ran into pretty much my entire graduating class. ridiculous. crazy new bar up the street is like the new hang out for all the 04 grads.

12.) Did you move anywhere? back to school... i dont know if that counts

13.) What sporting events did you go to? I went to a pirates game, an orioles game, and one slippery rock football game.

14.) What concerts did you go to? none

15.) Are you registered to vote? yeah

16.) If so, did you do your patriotic duty on Nov. 7? no

17.) Where do you live now? at the moment I am back in Columbia.

18.) Describe your birthday. craziness.. "Sleep-over" which was really only Jon Yates drunk on our couch. lol. and there was lots of watching of embarassing videos of me.

19.) What's the one thing you thought you would never do but did in 2007? yeah... not sure if i even want to say it on here... but people know. lol

20.) What is one thing you regretted this year? i need a job.

21.) What's something you learned about yourself? i am not ready to move on.

22.) Any new additions to your family? no.

23.) What was your best month? July/August. August

24.) What from pop culture will you remember 2006 by? 

25.) How would you rate this year with a scale from 1 (shitty) to 10 (excellent)? 7

Junior year has started now here at Slippery Rock. I have almost had all of my classes. But so far I have discovered that it is going to be a busy semester especially in two of my classes, which ironically I have the same professor for. I really like her, but she is in love with quizzes and I have them every class period basically. And I have an incredible amount of reading to do for those quizzes. I have problem read more in the last 2 days then I dont know, but I have read a whoooooole lot. But for the most part I think I am going to like my classes. I have all park and rec classes which is nice, no silly liberal studies.

hmm so i have been away from LJ for a while now. The summer is just so busy and I am just never home. I cant remember the last time that i wrote or what i even wrote about and I know that I havent had time to read anyones entries since before I left for camp. i wish that I could say that I had time to do that now, but no. I have to head back to camp again probably for the last time since there are only 10 days left of camp. Until then.
http://tarallen.livejournal.com/80503.html

Okay so camp has finally begun. Staff week just finished up on Friday. Lots of work was completed as well as lots of bruises and bug bites received. Many "special" things happened as well. I dont really know what more to say than that since I have limited time, but I will say that some of the staff is well not all there and wont shut up or just plain annoying. 

I got home Friday for my almost weekend off. I dont think i did anything other than washing clothes, eating and sleeping. On saturday I had to drive the station wagon, that pretty much sucked cause you can only drive it in second gear adn I had to drive on 29 and 32 so I was going slow and I felt like such an idiot. But  I had to go pick up some piece of furniture that my mom bought and the station wagon is the only place that it would fit. So i got that special job. But later my mom, brother and I went and saw cars. It was silly. At night Meredith and I hung out but no one else was around, sad times, so we basically just went to Target and then hung around my house and talked. 

I have to head back to camp in a little bit. Its raining now and I dont like it. I wont be home again until next Tuesday. So I believe this week is when I shall begin writing everyone letters, YAY!!
http://tarallen.livejournal.com/80355.html

Sooo my freedom of summer is almost over because I have to be at camp in a week, next friday night. It's sad though cause I feel like I havent done anything with my summer, nor have I gone anywhere. Last summer I did so many things before camp started, went to Colorado and Utah, went to 6 flags, DC, and hung out with all my friends. Now it seems like all I do watch TV and sit at home. I wish I could change that but I only have a week.

And I feel really distant from my friends especially everyone back in PA, but I guess thats because there IS a lot of distance, literally, between us. Sad times. But I expect everyone to write me happy little letters while I am at camp. My address is as follows:

Taralyn Trunk- Staff
BCMSR- Camp Oest
1929 Susquehanna Hall Rd
Whiteford, Md 21160

i dont think I have everyone's addresses sooo make sure I get those if you want me to write you a letter, otherwise write me first and include it and I will write back. Yay for mail.

ALLLL i did today was sit around and begin to watch season one of Alias. So far I have watched 8 episodes and that was all today. ugh. I need something to do with my life.

Yesterday we had our "Homecoming." It was quite silly and fun. We all got dressed up and went out to dinner at That's Amore. Many a people showed up. Laura, Amy R, Brooke, Justin, Amy C, Melanie, Meredith, Michelle, Amanda, and Myself. It was quite a nice dinner. I had never been there before but my ravioli was delicious. Meredith had the same and she enjoyed it too until she found traces of Ham. There isn't really much more to say about that, we ate and chatted. It was fun and nice to see everyone and those that we hadnt seen in FOREVER.

But when we got there is was hard to find a parking space cause Jazz Fest or something was going on. And it was even WORSE leaving cause the thing let out as we were leaving so we got in HORRIBLE traffic. Atleast some of us did. A few were able to slip out before it got bad cause they parked closer, but those of us high up in the farther away parking garage were trapped. It was BAD. I was able to run up and talk to Laura in her car and I even had to walk and inspect the traffic up ahead. I am NEVER going to a Jazz festival.

Today was a much slower day, but had more things involvved. Meredith and I went and took a walk around Centennial Lake since it was such a nice day, but we couldnt come up with something to do afterwards so we walked around my neighborhood and made stops at three of the local playgrounds. We amused ourselved taking pictures until we got the call from Julie saying that we could come over and hang out. 

SOoo we ate dinner with Julie and basically sat around and read Cosmo. It was quite enjoyable. Now my day is over and almost time for bed. sooo I dont know what. I guess I should get ready for that.

Adios.

Happy Skyscraper Day!

Today Ashlei, Megan and I went geocaching. The first and last caches that we attempted to be find we basically gave up on. For the first one we couldnt find where we were supposed to park and we didnt even see a trailhead anywhere nearby. Then the last one had a lot of tree cover so the GPS wasn't getting a good signal and couldnt decided which way it wanted up to go. We did find the second one that we looked for. I got some play-doh!!! It was rather exciting especially since yesterday i was sad that i didnt bring my play-doh and wouldnt have any for play-doh day.

After geocaching we were going to go to Walmart, but I didnt feel well so I came back to the dorms and slept for a little while. I just got up a few minutes ago. I feel better now, yay.

Last night we went and watched Crash over in McKay. It was a good movie, it was about diversity. I recommend it to all. Then afterward I was going to work on teh mountains of reading that i have to do. Yeah, that didnt happen. Ashlei and I ended up listening to silly songs and doing a bit of dancing. It twas fun but the homework still awaits... grrr.

oh yeah so at brunch today at the fluh, we definatley used styrafoam plates and cups and had plastic utensils. It was weird. But we were back to the normal stuff at dinner.

So Im back at SRU after driving lots yesterday. Classes started today and I guess they went well for being the first day. Nothing important really happed so its alright. My geology teacher is pretty cool, he is very enthusiastic about what he teaches. I got my books today as well. There are a whole lot of them. Grrrrrr.

Ashlei and I went to walmart today. yeah so i realized that i dont know how to get to the one in butler, but i figured it out after we got back. we ended up going to the one in new castle, oh well.

yeah did you know that you can make your turn signals so that they wont work at all? well i can. its not fun. the car hates me. But i bought it gas today for $2.55. It was exciting. Its definaletly more expensive than that in Maryland.
http://tarallen.livejournal.com/58812.html

So Jeremy and I went geocaching today and we made complete fools out of ourselves. The map for this one cache made it look like it was actually on the side of 83. Yeah it wasn't. But we didnt find that one out until after we had walked a little bit on the side of the road and passed some motorcyclists who thought that we were insane. They said something about how it wasn't a great place for a stroll and asked if we needed any help. Of course when we got close to the cache we realized that it was on the other side of the fence. Great. Well we got to the parking lot where it was hiding and we couldnt find it. Then a car drove up to us and the driver starting talking to us. Apparently it was the guy who had hidden the cache. He said that we were close cause otherwise he would have given us a hint. Well we never found it. Jeremy was disappointed cause he couldnt find the first cache that he went in search of. This from the guy who didn't know what geocaching was a few hours earlier. Boys are silly. But we didnt find some other ones later in the day so that made him happier.

yeah so thats my interesting story for the day.
http://tarallen.livejournal.com/58554.html

So as of today I have completed 2 more of my summer goals!!!

This morning, I do mean the wee hours of the morning, like 2am I finished reading Harry Potter, yay! Now the next time that Phil asks me if i have read any more i can tell him that i am done!! Thats exciting.

Also, quite recently I have finished my Senior year scrapbook, FINALLY. Seriously, it is about time, cause a whole year and then some have passed since then.



Anyway, today Julie, Meredith and I made our traditional gross, deathly sugary cupcakes. They just kill you they are soooooo sweeeeet. But they are enjoyable never the less. THey were actually kind of good this year though. I dont know why, it was the same recipe. We did add chocolate chips this year. Maybe that has something to do with it?
http://tarallen.livejournal.com/58304.html

The past few days well like 5, i have basically spent hanging out with amy r. Sometimes others would be there, but for the most part it has been the 2 of us. One day the Amys adn I sat at Baskin Robbins for like 2 hours. It was fun and all cause we got to talk, but we definatley needed other things to do besides sitting around eating. But then the plan for the next day was to go to Taco Bell and hang out there cause according to Amy R. that is where all the guys with hot cars hang out. 

Yeah so the 2 of us went and yeah there were no. So we left. Decided that we were going to go to the pool hall cause that was like the only thing that we knew was open besides Double T. I however didnt feel like paying for something that i could do in my basement. So them Amy suggested Annapolis, cause of the Navy guys that are there, but neither of us knew how to get there and we couldnt go home to get directions cause it was already 10:30 at night and i parents would wonder where we were going at that hour. so we ended up drivign to Baltimore instead.

We got there around 11pm and we got some food at Hard Rock. We had the craziest waiter who kept coming over and talking to us. OUr food took forever to come and all we did was order and appetizer. He ended up rambling ot us about how they had a rush on them at night cause there had been a baseball and a football game. ANd he apparently can tell the difference between football adn baseball people. Football people are rowdy and drink heavily while baseball people concentrate more.. yeah yeah whatever. Amy and i were confused cause she is a football person and i am baseball. Later he demonstrated how he had to tell the person making our food how to put it together. And he decided that we needed entertaining so he started to dance. it was quite strange. 

After we ate we felt sooo sick, but the food was good. We walked around Baltimore looking at all the decorated crabs. There were some pretty cool ones. Random guys kept yelling to us cause they were drunk. kinda scary. When we got to baltimore an old man actually told us not to stay out to late. Amy was like what a nice old man, he reminds me of my grandpa cause every old drunk man does. We eventually left the city at like 1:30 and went home. It was a good night. We actually got out of Howard County!!!

Today i basically did nothing. but atleast i got one important thing out of the way. I signed up for another class for the fall semester. Now i have 16 credits instead of the 13 that i originally scheduled. Yay i got into inclusive leisure services. Im glad about that.

That was probably the most important thing that i did today. I guess the next important thing is the fact that i am in the process of cleaning up my rooming and putting the massive amount of clothes and other belongings away that i took to camp. Actually its more than just what i took to camp. I still have clothes and stuff to put away from when I went out west!! so yeah i have alot cleaning and things to find places for. It is going to take me basically atleast until the end of the week to finish all of it.

That will leave me with 2 weeks left to do everything else that i must accomplish before school starts. Hopefully Anne and i will get to make our weekend trip to Deep Creek Lake which would be tons and tons of fun. And give us one last chance to hang out before i head out to PA. Plus there wouldn't be any crazy boy scouts around this time, yay. lol.

The Keys to Your Heart

You are attracted to those who have a split personality - cold as ice on the outside but hot as fire in the heart.
In love, you feel the most alive when your lover is creative and never lets you feel bored.
You'd like to your lover to think you are loyal and faithful... that you'll never change.
You would be forced to break up with someone who was emotional, moody, and difficult to please.
Your ideal relationship is lasting. You want a relationship that looks to the future... one you can grow with.
Your risk of cheating is zero. You care about society and morality. You would never break a commitment.
You think of marriage as something that will confine you. You are afraid of marriage.
In this moment, you think of love as commitment. Love only works when both people are totally devoted.
What Are The Keys To Your Heart?
